Using the output at: https://github.com/cmcntsh/statistics/blob/master/images/SimpleRegressionQuizOutput.pdf Does the Adverts variable violate the normality assumption?
Choice 1: Yes. The Shiro-Wilk test is significant and skewness/std error of skewness is greater than 2. But the sample size is large so it's OK to perform the regression analysis.
Choice 2: Yes. The normality assumption is violated and the regression should not be performed.
Choice 3: No. The Shapiro-Wilk test is not significant.
Choice 4: No. Skewness divided by std.error of skewness is less than 2.
